{
  "stem": "12491.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the bread we was cut long, like a roll, and we finished it all.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Eventually, I-- I did manage to get back to Krakow, when I wound up with my mother and my sister, again hoping that they would change their mind and be able to go back.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But what I did not realize that now the border is sealed to the point that I could not go back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this how I got stuck in the German part occupied of Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was talking to people who crossed the border coming into the German-- in the German side, and they found-- they told me about the difficulties which now is-- one is to encounter.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I pretty much got cold feet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I got-- I got--.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Since my mother and two sisters wouldn't want to go, I had a dilemma-- to stay with them, to go by my-- back by myself, and I decided to stay.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They still-- we still lived in our own apartment where we used-- where we lived before the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from time to time, the Germans surrounded a certain section of Jewish population and ransacked the apartment, took away whatever they told is of value, issued edicts that people have to give-- give away gold and et cetera, et cetera-- fur coats, whatever-- anything and everything of value.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there was no ghetto per se.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was kind of a ghetto or self-ordained by the Jews, who lived in Krakow, only in one section.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was Kazimierz.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We lived just outside that point-- that-- that part.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So when they surrounded the Kazimierz and for three or four days, and they conducted searches of all Jewish apartments and homes, we were actually excluded.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
